# Local market data & engine outputs (do not commit).
#
# The `data/` tree is organised as:
#   data/historical/<ticker>/  bulk historical archives (multi-GB, per-ticker)
#   data/raw/                  vendor snapshots downloaded at run time
#   data/processed/            intermediate/normalised extracts
#   data/generated/            everything the engine produces: benchmark
#                              reports, calibration tables, research CSVs,
#                              plots -- default output root for every module
#
# Standard "keep the tree, ignore the contents" pattern: exclude everything
# below the four roots, then re-include directory descents and .gitkeep
# sentinels so the skeleton stays in git for fresh clones.
data/raw/**
data/processed/**
data/generated/**
data/historical/**

!data/raw/**/
!data/processed/**/
!data/generated/**/
!data/historical/**/
!data/**/.gitkeep
!data/README.md

# Legacy: `spy_eod_*` archives at the repo root (before the reorg they
# lived here). Kept for backwards compatibility with clones that
# haven't been re-organised yet.
/spy_eod_*/

